.SH NAME
fur-graph - Output link graph in DOT format


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBfur graph [path] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Generate a Graphviz DOT representation of the inter-document link graph.
Nodes are markdown files, edges are links between them (standard markdown
links and [[wikilinks]]). Pipe to dot, neato, or other Graphviz tools to
render as an image.

.PP
An interactive graph is also available at /graph when using "fur serve".

.PP
Use --json for machine-readable output (nodes and edges with metadata).


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for graph

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	output as JSON (nodes and edges)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB-c\fP, \fB--config\fP=""
	config file path

.PP
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	enable verbose logging

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	disable colors (ascii theme)

.PP
\fB--theme\fP=""
	color theme (light|dark|auto|ascii)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  fur graph
  fur graph | dot -Tpng -o links.png
  fur graph --json | jq '.nodes | length'
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBfur(1)\fP


